Create a full-stack enterprise application with Angular (frontend) and Node.js (backend) using a clean, scalable architecture.

=====================
PROJECT REQUIREMENTS
=====================

Frontend: Angular (latest version)
Backend: Node.js with Express
Database: MySQL (or PostgreSQL)
UI Library: Angular Material
Excel Generation: xlsx library
Email Sending: Outlook SMTP (nodemailer)

=====================
FEATURES
=====================

1. DATA TABLE (FRONTEND)
- Fetch data from backend API and display in a table
- Use Angular Material table (mat-table)
- Columns should be dynamically generated based on API response
- Enable inline editing for each cell (input fields inside table)
- Track edited rows and fields (dirty state)

2. INLINE EDIT FUNCTIONALITY
- User should be able to click on any cell and edit value
- On blur or save click, update should be stored locally
- Provide a "Save Changes" button
- On save:
  → Send updated rows to backend via API (PUT request)
  → Backend updates database
  → UI refreshes with latest data

3. BACKEND APIs
Create REST APIs:
- GET /data → fetch all records
- PUT /data → update edited records in bulk
- POST /send-email → generate excel and send email

4. DATABASE LAYER
- Create a sample table with 5–6 columns (id, name, status, amount, date, etc.)
- Use a repository/service pattern
- Handle bulk updates efficiently

5. EXCEL GENERATION
- On clicking "Send" button:
  → Backend fetches latest data
  → Convert JSON to Excel using xlsx
  → Generate file in memory (no disk storage)

6. EMAIL FUNCTIONALITY
- Use nodemailer with Outlook SMTP
- Send email with:
  → Subject: "Data Validation Required"
  → Body: simple message
  → Attachment: generated Excel file

7. UI ACTIONS
- Buttons:
  → "Save Changes"
  → "Send for Validation"
- Disable Send button until data is saved
- Show success/error notifications

